# Next.js 16 + TypeScript project standards

## Stack

- Next.js **16.2.1** (App Router), TypeScript **strict**, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui (Radix), Lucide React, Zod.

## Code style

- No `any`; prefer interfaces/types or Zod-inferred types.
- Components: **arrow functions**, **PascalCase** filenames (e.g. `UserButton.tsx`).
- Default **Server Components**; `'use client'` only for interactivity, hooks, or browser APIs.
- DRY/SOLID; validate inputs with Zod on boundaries (Server Actions, Route Handlers, server utilities).

## Layout

- App routes: `web/app/` (kebab-case route segments).
- `web/components/ui` — shadcn primitives; `web/components/shared` — reusable product components.
- `web/lib` — server utilities, clients; `web/hooks`; `web/types`.
- Utils/hooks: camelCase files (e.g. `useLocalStorage.ts`).

## CSS / UI

- Tailwind only; mobile-first; avoid inline `style={}` (exceptions: truly dynamic values with good reason).
- No raw HTML project at repo root for new features — use the `web/` Next app.

## Agent workflow

- Non-trivial work: short plan in chat, then confirm before large diffs.
- Before features needing secrets: check `web/.env.example` and document new vars there.
- After significant changes: `npm run build` and/or `npm run lint` from `web/`.
- Async server code: try/catch + structured errors; never trust unvalidated input.
